1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:00:03,350 --> 00:00:06,770
Wow... An elephant bluefin tuna, huh?

3
00:00:06,770 --> 00:00:09,900
Ahhh! I can't wait to cook it!

4
00:00:01,560 --> 00:00:03,350
Ah! That was fun!

5
00:00:10,630 --> 00:00:11,400
Huh?

6
00:00:14,230 --> 00:00:15,770
What's the matter, Nami?

7
00:00:15,770 --> 00:00:17,420
There was a shift in the air...

8
00:00:17,420 --> 00:00:18,280
The air?

9
00:00:18,280 --> 00:00:19,750
It's gonna rain.

10
00:00:19,750 --> 00:00:21,750
Huh? When the weather is this nice?

11
00:00:21,750 --> 00:00:23,210
There's no doubt about it.

12
00:00:24,330 --> 00:00:26,510
Hey, someone's on
the execution platform!

13
00:00:26,510 --> 00:00:27,750
Who the heck is that?

14
00:00:29,330 --> 00:00:34,880
That old man said that the King of
the Pirates died here twenty-two years ago.

15
00:00:34,880 --> 00:00:35,840
He showed up?!

16
00:00:35,840 --> 00:00:40,310
Yes! We watched over the square as ordered,
and then the man from the wanted poster...!

17
00:00:40,310 --> 00:00:41,600
Okay.

18
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:43,550
Let's go flashily.

19
00:00:45,640 --> 00:00:50,250
He walked right up to it...
Just you wait, brat.

20
00:00:56,570 --> 00:01:03,500
Wow! So this what it looked like
for the King of the Pirates...

21
00:01:04,390 --> 00:01:05,960
Please wait!

22
00:01:05,960 --> 00:01:07,940
Captain Smoker!

23
00:01:07,940 --> 00:01:09,920
Come along, Tashigi.

24
00:03:01,350 --> 00:03:06,160
Hey! You up there!

25
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:09,590
Come down this instant!

26
00:03:09,590 --> 00:03:11,290
Why?!

27
00:03:11,290 --> 00:03:15,690
That's a special execution platform
used by the World Government!

28
00:03:15,690 --> 00:03:17,920
Come down right now!

29
00:03:21,470 --> 00:03:24,690
Hmph! Now's not
the time for small fries.

30
00:03:24,690 --> 00:03:25,680
Hm?

31
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:29,610
I've been looking for you, Luffy.
Long time no see...

32
00:03:32,980 --> 00:03:38,610
Don't tell me you've forgotten my face.

33
00:03:39,070 --> 00:03:40,980
How pretty!

34
00:03:40,980 --> 00:03:42,010
She's stunning!

35
00:03:42,010 --> 00:03:43,850
She's a woman of unrivaled beauty!

36
00:03:43,850 --> 00:03:46,490
Her skin looks so smooth.

37
00:03:46,490 --> 00:03:49,460
I don't know anyone like you.

38
00:03:49,830 --> 00:03:51,290
Who the heck are you?

39
00:03:51,290 --> 00:03:53,840
I'll never forget you...

40
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:57,010
because you're the first man
to have ever hit me.

41
00:03:57,010 --> 00:03:59,490
What? I hit you?

42
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:05,830
When your passionate fist struck me...

43
00:04:08,850 --> 00:04:10,890
Oh, it felt great...

44
00:04:15,070 --> 00:04:20,530
Fellas... On these seas,
who's the fairest of them all?

45
00:04:20,530 --> 00:04:23,530
– That'd be you!
– That'd be you!

46
00:04:23,530 --> 00:04:25,430
That's right. It's me.

47
00:04:25,430 --> 00:04:30,040
There isn't a man in this world
that doesn't bow before my beauty.

48
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:33,040
And I do love a strong man.

49
00:04:33,930 --> 00:04:37,500
I'll make you mine, Luffy.

50
00:04:38,050 --> 00:04:38,970
Shut up!

51
00:04:38,970 --> 00:04:40,800
No way! Who the heck are you?

52
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:42,420
Still haven't figured it out?!

53
00:04:43,570 --> 00:04:46,840
This is the police! Come quietly, lady!

54
00:04:47,300 --> 00:04:50,730
You're under arrest for
assaulting our police captain!

55
00:04:51,270 --> 00:04:54,270
And you! Get off
the execution platform!

56
00:04:54,270 --> 00:04:57,020
Oh? Who'd you say you'd arrest?

57
00:04:57,020 --> 00:05:00,390
Lieutenant, we have
a problem! She's beautiful!

58
00:05:00,390 --> 00:05:02,690
Beauty be damned! Arrest her!

59
00:05:02,690 --> 00:05:05,910
Sh-She's so beautiful
that she's dazzling!

60
00:05:05,910 --> 00:05:07,290
How nice!

61
00:05:09,170 --> 00:05:10,950
We're being bombed!

62
00:05:10,950 --> 00:05:11,500
She'll get hit!

63
00:05:15,370 --> 00:05:16,750
Wh-What the...?!

64
00:05:16,750 --> 00:05:18,330
The fountain slid right past...!

65
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:20,710
What just happened?!

66
00:05:23,030 --> 00:05:26,170
That was dangerous, you know.

67
00:05:26,170 --> 00:05:32,980
Flashily sorry. But your smooth skin is
unharmed, of course. So no harm done...

68
00:05:32,980 --> 00:05:35,270
fairest Alvida!

69
00:05:35,850 --> 00:05:37,810
Huh? Alvida?

70
00:05:41,190 --> 00:05:42,900
I don't see Alvida.

71
00:05:42,900 --> 00:05:45,070
I'm Alvida, you blockhead!

72
00:05:45,460 --> 00:05:48,490
Really? You don't look like her at all...

73
00:05:50,090 --> 00:05:53,420
I changed after eating a devil fruit.

74
00:05:53,420 --> 00:05:56,660
The name of the fruit is...
the Smooth-Smooth Fruit!

75
00:05:57,770 --> 00:06:02,630
All attacks slide right off my skin
and leave me unharmed.

76
00:06:02,990 --> 00:06:07,420
Unfortunately, my beauty
couldn't be improved that much.

77
00:06:07,900 --> 00:06:12,080
There was one big change, though.
Why, yes, my freckles are gone.

78
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:14,390
N-No, that's not really what I meant.

79
00:06:14,390 --> 00:06:16,150
After becoming a new person,

80
00:06:16,150 --> 00:06:20,990
I teamed up with a certain someone
because he also wanted to find you.

81
00:06:29,210 --> 00:06:33,740
Now, the main star can
make his flashy entrance!

82
00:06:33,740 --> 00:06:35,650
Monkey D. Luffy!

83
00:06:35,650 --> 00:06:38,210
Since the day you sent me flying,

84
00:06:38,210 --> 00:06:40,770
I've been obsessed with
getting revenge on you.

85
00:06:40,770 --> 00:06:44,390
That alone led me to
finally find my crew.

86
00:06:44,390 --> 00:06:48,710
It was indeed a great adventure.
I was missing parts of my body.

87
00:06:48,710 --> 00:06:51,390
I laughed, I went through hell,
and I made new friends.

88
00:06:51,390 --> 00:06:53,810
I call it "Little Buggy's Big Adventure."

89
00:06:53,810 --> 00:06:55,390
You see, Buggy was...

90
00:06:55,730 --> 00:06:57,360
Why am I telling you any of this?!

91
00:06:57,610 --> 00:07:00,210
What? Wait, what
was your name again?

92
00:07:00,210 --> 00:07:03,770
Bogey... No, Boogie.
Maybe it was Behee...? Or not...

93
00:07:03,770 --> 00:07:04,820
Oh, yeah!

94
00:07:04,820 --> 00:07:06,210
Buffoon!

95
00:07:09,150 --> 00:07:12,130
Buffoon?! Stop messing around!

96
00:07:12,130 --> 00:07:15,330
You're as irritating as ever, you moron!

97
00:07:15,950 --> 00:07:17,580
Th-That's Buggy the Clown!

98
00:07:17,580 --> 00:07:18,950
They're p-pirates!

99
00:07:19,290 --> 00:07:23,880
It's the Buggy Pirates!

100
00:07:24,290 --> 00:07:28,210
People! Remain flashily where you are!

101
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:34,010
I'm gonna show you all
just how scary I am.

102
00:07:35,470 --> 00:07:37,180
Oh! It's Buggy!

103
00:07:37,180 --> 00:07:39,730
You just remembered it?!

104
00:07:41,730 --> 00:07:43,520
Wh-What's going on?

105
00:07:44,050 --> 00:07:49,480
Long time no see, rubber man.
How's Roronoa Zoro doing?

106
00:07:49,480 --> 00:07:52,360
Okay, Cabaji. Good job.

107
00:07:55,910 --> 00:08:00,310
I ask that my hundreds of billions of
followers around the world watch closely!

108
00:08:00,310 --> 00:08:03,830
We're about to host a super
flashy public execution!

109
00:08:03,830 --> 00:08:09,630
Monkey D. Luffy! You can't
move even an inch now.

110
00:08:09,630 --> 00:08:11,890
You should feel honored, Straw Hat!

111
00:08:11,890 --> 00:08:15,050
You get to die in the same place
as the King of the Pirates.

112
00:08:27,230 --> 00:08:30,110
The atmospheric pressure
is dropping like crazy.

113
00:08:30,110 --> 00:08:32,690
I've never seen such
a bizarre drop before.

114
00:08:32,690 --> 00:08:35,450
Now that you mention it,
the wind does feel different...

115
00:08:36,330 --> 00:08:38,610
A storm is gonna hit this island!

116
00:08:38,610 --> 00:08:40,200
A-A storm?

117
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:43,110
We'd better hurry back to
the ship or we'll be in trouble.

118
00:08:43,110 --> 00:08:44,640
Will it be a big one?

119
00:08:44,640 --> 00:08:45,290
Hey...!

120
00:08:45,300 --> 00:08:45,670
Hm?

121
00:08:45,670 --> 00:08:47,010
Zoro!

122
00:08:47,010 --> 00:08:48,960
Have you seen him?

123
00:08:48,960 --> 00:08:50,210
You mean Luffy?

124
00:08:51,910 --> 00:08:54,880
– Pirates are here!
– Pirates are here!

125
00:08:55,330 --> 00:08:56,520
Pirates are here!

126
00:08:56,520 --> 00:08:57,160
Run!

127
00:08:57,160 --> 00:08:59,010
It's Buggy the Clown!

128
00:08:59,010 --> 00:09:00,410
What'd they say?!

129
00:09:00,410 --> 00:09:01,970
Buggy the Clown!

130
00:09:07,270 --> 00:09:09,050
What? Then...

131
00:09:09,060 --> 00:09:10,190
Y-Yes, sir!

132
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:15,010
In addition to Straw Hat Luffy,
Buggy the Clown and Iron Club Alvida,

133
00:09:15,010 --> 00:09:20,390
both being notorious East Blue pirates,
have arrived to take over the square!

134
00:09:21,450 --> 00:09:23,610
Right under my nose...

135
00:09:24,810 --> 00:09:26,540
What arrogant scum.

136
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:29,420
What should we do, Captain Smoker?

137
00:09:30,690 --> 00:09:32,910
Unit one will set up on the sea!

138
00:09:32,910 --> 00:09:35,750
Unit two will secretly surround
the square in the streets.

139
00:09:35,750 --> 00:09:38,590
The rest will stand by within
firing range of the square.

140
00:09:39,230 --> 00:09:39,970
That is all!

141
00:09:39,970 --> 00:09:40,850
Yes, sir!

142
00:09:41,870 --> 00:09:43,620
Give this order to unit one.

143
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:43,930
Yes sir?

144
00:09:44,570 --> 00:09:47,800
"Destroy any pirate ships
as soon as you see them.

145
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:53,400
Don't let any pirates off
this island. Not a single one."

146
00:09:59,430 --> 00:10:00,260
An execution!

147
00:10:00,260 --> 00:10:01,580
An execution is starting!

148
00:10:01,580 --> 00:10:04,870
Buggy the Clown will be
executing Straw Hat Luffy!

149
00:10:04,870 --> 00:10:06,990
Luffy's gonna be executed?!

150
00:10:06,990 --> 00:10:08,470
That idiot!

151
00:10:08,470 --> 00:10:09,430
Let's go!

152
00:10:09,430 --> 00:10:10,810
Take care of this!

153
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:14,920
S-S-S-Sanji!

154
00:10:14,920 --> 00:10:17,010
Treat it like a lady! Got it?!

155
00:10:17,010 --> 00:10:17,590
Oops!

156
00:10:18,030 --> 00:10:19,740
We have to hurry, too!

157
00:10:19,740 --> 00:10:21,970
Hey! Hey, N-N-Nami! Where're we going?!

158
00:10:21,970 --> 00:10:23,840
The harbor, of course!

159
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:26,370
Th-The harbor? Oh, makes sense!

160
00:10:28,810 --> 00:10:30,350
Captain Smoker! Please take a look.

161
00:10:30,350 --> 00:10:32,370
Things are getting weird.

162
00:10:33,310 --> 00:10:33,980
Hm?

163
00:10:33,980 --> 00:10:35,940
Wha...! Th-That kid...!

164
00:10:36,890 --> 00:10:38,150
What's he doing?

165
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:44,070
Monkey D. Luffy. This can't be!
It looks like he's about to be killed!

166
00:10:44,070 --> 00:10:46,110
Captain, are we
swooping in right away?

167
00:10:46,110 --> 00:10:47,540
Idiot. Don't be hasty.

168
00:10:48,030 --> 00:10:51,230
A pirate is about to kill another pirate.

169
00:10:51,230 --> 00:10:53,790
This is great. They're
saving us the trouble.

170
00:10:55,050 --> 00:10:57,880
Listen up! Once Straw Hat's head rolls,

171
00:10:57,880 --> 00:11:01,260
surround Buggy, Alvida,
and those with them!

172
00:11:01,260 --> 00:11:02,340
Don't give 'em time to think!

173
00:11:06,630 --> 00:11:13,740
Pirate Monkey D. Luffy is a criminal
and will be flashily executed for...

174
00:11:13,740 --> 00:11:15,790
pissing me off with his attitude!

175
00:11:18,410 --> 00:11:20,240
Live it up flashily!

176
00:11:23,650 --> 00:11:25,870
This is my first time
seeing an execution.

177
00:11:25,870 --> 00:11:28,250
We're executing you.

178
00:11:28,250 --> 00:11:29,180
Hm?

179
00:11:29,920 --> 00:11:31,740
What?! Stop joking!

180
00:11:31,740 --> 00:11:33,380
You stop joking!

181
00:11:33,380 --> 00:11:36,090
Take this board off! You bastard!

182
00:11:34,170 --> 00:11:40,350
And now, the public execution
will flashily commence!

183
00:11:36,090 --> 00:11:40,350
Take it off! You tricked me!
You're a jerk! You bastard!

184
00:11:40,350 --> 00:11:45,350
Ahhh!! Stop it! Ahhh!
I don't wanna die!

185
00:11:46,110 --> 00:11:48,810
There's a big cumulus cloud
in the sky to the east!

186
00:11:48,810 --> 00:11:53,690
A storm is coming. It's
gonna be unimaginably big...

187
00:11:54,470 --> 00:11:58,610
If Buggy, Luffy, and the others
go crazy, the Marines will take action.

188
00:11:58,610 --> 00:12:02,260
We're done for if the ship is washed
out to sea when we have to escape.

189
00:12:02,260 --> 00:12:03,530
Yeah, this is urgent!

190
00:12:04,110 --> 00:12:07,530
The Marines may have
already made their move.

191
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:10,730
The Going Merry is in danger!

192
00:12:11,630 --> 00:12:14,920
Th-The Going Merry
will end up in Marine hands?

193
00:12:16,230 --> 00:12:18,750
Come on, Nami! H-Hurry up!

194
00:12:18,750 --> 00:12:20,470
Wait for me!

195
00:12:21,590 --> 00:12:23,630
Hurry to the harbor!

196
00:12:24,020 --> 00:12:28,040
♪ Riding around on the Richie Bike! ♪

197
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:33,440
♪ Who's that man?
Who? Who? Who's that man?! ♪

198
00:12:34,180 --> 00:12:36,230
♪ Me! ♪

199
00:12:36,630 --> 00:12:39,530
So this is the rubber guy's ship...

200
00:12:42,550 --> 00:12:45,110
It's bigger than his first,
like he's a real pirate...

201
00:12:45,110 --> 00:12:49,770
It's about time for him to get
flashily executed by Captain Buggy!

202
00:12:51,110 --> 00:12:57,210
However...! Just in case the rubber guy,
who has no chance of escaping,

203
00:12:57,210 --> 00:12:58,630
happens to escape...

204
00:12:58,630 --> 00:13:01,250
♪ It's our duty to burn this ship! ♪

205
00:13:06,050 --> 00:13:10,400
I'm sorry. I won't do it again.
Please let me go.

206
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:11,770
Why would I do that, idiot?!

207
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:15,620
Hmph! This is what happens
when someone goes against us.

208
00:13:15,620 --> 00:13:19,190
I guess this is it for
the man I had my eye on...

209
00:13:19,530 --> 00:13:22,190
Since you have a big audience,

210
00:13:22,190 --> 00:13:25,650
do you wanna say
something before you die?

211
00:13:27,430 --> 00:13:28,950
No? Well, that's okay.

212
00:13:28,950 --> 00:13:34,330
It wouldn't matter anyway
since you're about to die.

213
00:13:36,460 --> 00:13:40,390
I'm the man who's gonna be
King of the Pirates!

214
00:13:47,730 --> 00:13:49,050
Wha...?

215
00:13:49,050 --> 00:13:52,010
D-Did he just say
"King of the Pirates"?!

216
00:13:52,390 --> 00:13:54,650
In this town, of all places...

217
00:13:54,650 --> 00:13:57,020
What a crazy thing to say...

218
00:13:57,020 --> 00:14:00,900
Well then, I guess this is it...
you rubber twerp.

219
00:14:04,710 --> 00:14:06,240
Stop...

220
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:06,820
Wh-What?

221
00:14:06,820 --> 00:14:07,950
– ...the execution!
– ...the execution!

222
00:14:07,950 --> 00:14:08,410
What?

223
00:14:12,330 --> 00:14:14,160
Zoro! Sanji!

224
00:14:15,460 --> 00:14:19,050
It's Pirate Hunter Z-Zoro!

225
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:20,960
Zoro?!

226
00:14:22,380 --> 00:14:26,880
Ah, there you are, Zoro!
But you arrived a moment too late!

227
00:14:27,630 --> 00:14:29,690
– We'll bring down...
– ...that execution platform!

228
00:14:30,750 --> 00:14:32,350
Roronoa Zoro...

229
00:14:34,950 --> 00:14:36,890
Guys... get them!

230
00:14:36,890 --> 00:14:38,850
Leave it to us!

231
00:14:38,850 --> 00:14:40,810
Big Sis Alvida!

232
00:14:45,030 --> 00:14:45,860
Out of our way!

233
00:14:54,150 --> 00:14:57,040
Not even Zoro can stop me now!

234
00:14:57,040 --> 00:15:01,370
This is the end of your captain!

235
00:15:01,370 --> 00:15:03,050
Damn bastard!

236
00:15:06,670 --> 00:15:09,510
If I could just cut down the platform...

237
00:15:10,090 --> 00:15:11,010
Listen.

238
00:15:11,010 --> 00:15:14,730
The instant Monkey D. Luffy's head falls,
we're to attack all at once!

239
00:15:17,350 --> 00:15:19,140
All units. Prepare for battle.

240
00:15:19,140 --> 00:15:20,410
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

241
00:15:22,610 --> 00:15:24,110
Zoro! Sanji!

242
00:15:24,570 --> 00:15:26,520
Usopp! Nami!

243
00:15:24,110 --> 00:15:25,310
Hurry up!

244
00:15:25,310 --> 00:15:26,520
This is heavy!

245
00:15:27,610 --> 00:15:28,490
Sorry.

246
00:15:29,490 --> 00:15:30,740
I'm... dead.

247
00:15:30,740 --> 00:15:31,780
I'm... dead.

248
00:15:33,510 --> 00:15:34,290
Idiot...!

249
00:15:35,410 --> 00:15:37,300
Don't say something so stupid!

250
00:15:37,300 --> 00:15:38,590
He smiled!

251
00:16:27,210 --> 00:16:29,050
I'm still alive!

252
00:16:29,630 --> 00:16:31,050
Neat!

253
00:16:36,510 --> 00:16:39,390
H-Hey, do you believe in God?

254
00:16:37,350 --> 00:16:39,390
Phew, lucky me.

255
00:16:39,390 --> 00:16:42,490
Stop talking nonsense.
Let's get out of this town already!

256
00:16:39,390 --> 00:16:41,890
I was worried for a moment.

257
00:16:43,050 --> 00:16:45,110
It's just one thing after another.

258
00:16:50,130 --> 00:16:52,740
Now! Corner the pirates!

259
00:16:52,740 --> 00:16:55,890
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

260
00:16:56,650 --> 00:16:57,780
Here they come!

261
00:17:03,910 --> 00:17:08,290
Amazing! Amazing!
It's suddenly gotten crazy!

262
00:17:08,290 --> 00:17:10,750
Amazing! Ahh! Amazing!

263
00:17:10,750 --> 00:17:11,540
Hey, Luffy!

264
00:17:11,540 --> 00:17:13,390
Ahhh... Z-Zoro!

265
00:17:13,390 --> 00:17:15,840
I get that this is exciting,
but we've gotta go!

266
00:17:16,190 --> 00:17:20,060
We'd better hurry back to the ship or
we'll never be able to leave the island.

267
00:17:20,450 --> 00:17:22,350
We won't be able to
enter the Grand Line!

268
00:17:22,350 --> 00:17:24,350
What?! That's not good!

269
00:17:26,100 --> 00:17:27,940
The Straw Hats are running!

270
00:17:28,290 --> 00:17:29,520
Capture them!

271
00:17:29,520 --> 00:17:30,860
Go after them!

272
00:17:35,150 --> 00:17:36,990
Why did he smile?

273
00:17:38,150 --> 00:17:40,470
Did he know he'd be saved?

274
00:17:41,390 --> 00:17:47,370
No. In that moment, he genuinely
thought his life was over.

275
00:17:47,730 --> 00:17:52,130
He was prepared
to accept death and smiled.

276
00:17:52,130 --> 00:17:54,270
Captain, we have to
apprehend the pirates.

277
00:17:54,270 --> 00:18:00,350
Hey... have you seen a pirate who
smiled on the execution platform?

278
00:18:02,710 --> 00:18:05,710
N-Never! Even if they're acting tough,

279
00:18:05,710 --> 00:18:09,100
at the moment of death,
they all turn pale and die in despair.

280
00:18:09,100 --> 00:18:12,860
That man in the straw hat smiled...

281
00:18:13,650 --> 00:18:20,330
just like the Pirate King, twenty-two years ago in this town...

282
00:18:20,330 --> 00:18:23,660
Gold Roger smiled on
the execution platform.

283
00:18:32,710 --> 00:18:33,730
Captain...

284
00:18:34,950 --> 00:18:36,630
Where did Straw Hat go?

285
00:18:36,630 --> 00:18:40,450
He ran toward the sea, sir.

286
00:18:40,450 --> 00:18:45,050
What's unit one doing? They should've
destroyed their ship by now.

287
00:18:45,870 --> 00:18:49,730
Well... They had to return for
refitting because they couldn't

288
00:18:49,730 --> 00:18:52,350
light the gunpowder
due to the sudden rain...

289
00:18:52,350 --> 00:18:53,940
What?!

290
00:18:53,940 --> 00:18:58,270
A reserve unit is currently
moving to attack the ship instead.

291
00:18:58,270 --> 00:19:03,620
Captain Smoker! If we let them set
sail now, they'll enter the Grand Line!

292
00:19:04,850 --> 00:19:09,650
The wind is blowing westward... Their ship will have a tailwind.

293
00:19:11,370 --> 00:19:13,910
Are these all coincidences?

294
00:19:15,730 --> 00:19:19,630
It's as if the heavens have
plans for that young man.

295
00:19:20,950 --> 00:19:23,970
We'd better hurry
or we'll be in trouble!

296
00:19:22,170 --> 00:19:25,060
We're gonna make it
to the Grand Line like this!

297
00:19:24,390 --> 00:19:26,430
I'm White Hound Smoker.

298
00:19:26,510 --> 00:19:31,190
On my honor as a Marine Headquarters
captain, I won't let that man leave this island!

299
00:19:37,390 --> 00:19:39,610
What's with this storm?!

300
00:19:39,630 --> 00:19:42,530
If we don't leave soon,
we'll be stuck here.

301
00:19:42,530 --> 00:19:45,200
Nami's right that we should
hurry back to the ship!

302
00:19:47,850 --> 00:19:50,540
Attacking me is a waste of time.

303
00:19:50,540 --> 00:19:55,040
There isn't a man alive
who can touch my smooth skin.

304
00:19:58,910 --> 00:20:01,460
I just saw a field of flowers...

305
00:20:01,460 --> 00:20:03,870
Captain Buggy, you're alive!

306
00:20:03,870 --> 00:20:04,800
No way I'd die!

307
00:20:05,120 --> 00:20:06,530
Buggy, this isn't good!

308
00:20:06,530 --> 00:20:08,600
Marines from HQ
aren't going to give up.

309
00:20:08,600 --> 00:20:11,490
Hmph. Like I care where
the Marines stick their nose...

310
00:20:11,490 --> 00:20:13,560
Whose nose did you say
is sticking out?!

311
00:20:13,560 --> 00:20:15,530
I didn't say anything like that!

312
00:20:18,320 --> 00:20:19,450
What's the plan?!

313
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:22,390
Gum-Gum! Go after Gum-Gum!

314
00:20:22,390 --> 00:20:25,270
Mohji and Richie will have
burned down his ship by now.

315
00:20:25,270 --> 00:20:27,230
He can't get off of this island.

316
00:20:27,230 --> 00:20:30,060
We'll kick his ass
and leave this island, guys!

317
00:20:30,060 --> 00:20:31,310
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

318
00:20:31,310 --> 00:20:32,540
Motor!

319
00:20:32,540 --> 00:20:34,420
– Yes, Captain!
– Yes, Captain!

320
00:20:34,740 --> 00:20:36,670
Chop-Chop Buggy!

321
00:20:36,670 --> 00:20:37,380
Here we go!

322
00:20:37,750 --> 00:20:39,670
Igniting the bomb engine!

323
00:20:42,300 --> 00:20:44,260
Set the slope!

324
00:20:44,260 --> 00:20:46,370
– Yes, Big Sis Alvida!
– Yes, Big Sis Alvida!

325
00:20:46,370 --> 00:20:47,800
No Friction...

326
00:20:50,410 --> 00:20:52,640
Smooth-Smooth Tracks!

327
00:20:58,520 --> 00:21:00,900
Don't let the pirates get away!

328
00:21:06,830 --> 00:21:08,780
Wh... What's this smoke?!

329
00:21:10,850 --> 00:21:13,370
What the hell...?!

330
00:21:13,370 --> 00:21:15,170
White Out!

331
00:21:19,470 --> 00:21:21,790
Smoker!

332
00:21:21,790 --> 00:21:25,630
I don't have time for you small fries!

333
00:21:26,020 --> 00:21:27,280
H-He's too strong!

334
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:29,190
The power of the
Smoke-Smoke Fruit...

335
00:21:29,190 --> 00:21:31,690
He took down Buggy's crew
in a split second...

336
00:21:33,370 --> 00:21:34,390
Fire!

337
00:21:40,730 --> 00:21:43,100
Captain! He caught
us all in one fell swoop!

338
00:21:43,100 --> 00:21:45,100
How dare you, Smoker!

339
00:21:45,100 --> 00:21:49,240
What's with this annoying steel net?!
Firing a weird pistol like that...

340
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:53,770
The Marines developed this cage shot
as a way to deal with devil fruit powers.

341
00:21:53,770 --> 00:21:54,700
Dammit!

342
00:21:55,850 --> 00:21:59,210
Bring me the Billower Bike!
I'm going after Straw Hat!

343
00:21:59,210 --> 00:22:00,210
Yes, sir!

344
00:22:02,610 --> 00:22:04,220
Dammit!

345
00:22:04,220 --> 00:22:10,110
Why the sudden downpour,
when we've gotta burn this ship down?!

346
00:22:12,180 --> 00:22:16,030
Dammit! This is bad, Richie!
We can't get a fire going like this!

347
00:22:16,030 --> 00:22:17,210
One more time!

348
00:22:20,170 --> 00:22:23,480
Be patient, Richie! I'll feed you later.

349
00:22:25,250 --> 00:22:27,090
What're you doing?!

350
00:22:27,700 --> 00:22:29,280
Mohji!

351
00:22:30,690 --> 00:22:32,990
Oh, if it isn't that thief woman.

352
00:22:33,710 --> 00:22:36,290
Go, Richie!

353
00:22:42,250 --> 00:22:44,670
Lethal Fresh Egg Star!

354
00:22:51,350 --> 00:22:52,710
You...

355
00:22:52,710 --> 00:22:54,600
Damn! The rain made my hand slip!

356
00:22:57,090 --> 00:23:01,230
Richie! Just once, could you not...!

357
00:23:01,860 --> 00:23:03,400
Now! Let's get on the ship!

358
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:04,150
Yeah!

359
00:23:04,150 --> 00:23:07,110
Hold it! You have to get past me!

360
00:23:08,070 --> 00:23:10,860
I am Mohji, first mate of
Buggy the Clown's pirate crew!

361
00:23:10,860 --> 00:23:13,970
I won't let you set even
one foot aboard this sh–

362
00:23:15,740 --> 00:23:17,660
Prepare to fire!

363
00:23:18,360 --> 00:23:19,370
The Marines!

364
00:23:19,370 --> 00:23:20,420
This is bad!

365
00:23:20,770 --> 00:23:21,890
Aim!

366
00:23:23,910 --> 00:23:25,410
Fire!

367
00:23:29,890 --> 00:23:33,170
Contact the cannon unit!
We'll capture the pirate ship!

368
00:23:33,170 --> 00:23:33,720
Yes, sir!

369
00:23:33,720 --> 00:23:35,030
N-N-N-Nami!

370
00:23:35,030 --> 00:23:36,010
Yeah!

371
00:23:47,910 --> 00:23:49,650
Which direction is the sea?

372
00:23:49,650 --> 00:23:53,110
I can't tell where we're going
because of all this rain!

373
00:23:53,110 --> 00:23:54,630
There they are!

374
00:23:56,330 --> 00:23:59,250
Persistent bastards!
Should we stop and fight?!

375
00:23:59,250 --> 00:24:00,600
We don't have time.

376
00:24:01,460 --> 00:24:02,000
Oh?

377
00:24:02,500 --> 00:24:04,920
Who's that lady?!

378
00:24:05,260 --> 00:24:06,340
Hm?

379
00:24:06,890 --> 00:24:10,260
I didn't realize you were
Roronoa Zoro, and a pirate at that.

380
00:24:10,870 --> 00:24:12,880
You gonna take this sword, too?

381
00:24:14,550 --> 00:24:18,510
You... You lied to me!

382
00:24:18,510 --> 00:24:22,020
What?! What'd you do to her?!

383
00:24:22,020 --> 00:24:24,730
You never asked for my name, is all.

384
00:24:25,040 --> 00:24:26,750
I never lied to you.

385
00:24:27,790 --> 00:24:32,490
Villains like you can't be allowed
to carry a sword of such renown!

386
00:24:32,490 --> 00:24:35,490
I lay claim to the named
blade Wado Ichimonji!

387
00:24:44,730 --> 00:24:47,750
You son of a bitch!
How dare you attack a lady!

388
00:24:47,750 --> 00:24:49,090
Go on ahead.

389
00:24:50,390 --> 00:24:51,230
Let's go.

390
00:24:53,310 --> 00:24:57,510
Hey, Zoro! If you hurt
the lady, I won't forgive you!

391
00:24:57,510 --> 00:24:58,800
Sergeant Major Tashigi!

392
00:25:16,370 --> 00:25:19,830
This is one sword
you won't be getting.

393
00:25:20,450 --> 00:25:22,390
Sergeant Major Tashigi lost...

394
00:25:22,390 --> 00:25:24,630
But she's the Sergeant Major Tashigi...

395
00:25:25,870 --> 00:25:28,050
So long. I'm in a hurry, so...

396
00:25:32,750 --> 00:25:34,190
Why not finish me off?!

397
00:25:35,230 --> 00:25:37,680
Is it because I'm a woman?!

398
00:25:40,030 --> 00:25:42,670
You're lucky, Zoro.
You were born a boy.

399
00:25:44,010 --> 00:25:46,330
Men might be physically
stronger than women,

400
00:25:46,330 --> 00:25:49,150
but it's so insulting that
you won't fight seriously!

401
00:25:49,620 --> 00:25:54,670
There's no way you understand what it
feels like to wish you were born a boy!

402
00:25:54,670 --> 00:25:57,490
I don't carry a sword as an accessory!

403
00:25:59,110 --> 00:26:01,280
I can't stand knowing that you exist!

404
00:26:02,910 --> 00:26:05,840
I'll just tell you! It's your face!

405
00:26:05,840 --> 00:26:08,770
You look exactly like my
good friend who died long ago!

406
00:26:08,770 --> 00:26:12,070
And now you're saying
the same thing she used to!

407
00:26:12,070 --> 00:26:14,380
Who are you to imitate
her, you copycat?!

408
00:26:14,380 --> 00:26:17,050
The hell...?! Grow up
and think before you speak!

409
00:26:17,050 --> 00:26:18,890
I am who I am!

410
00:26:18,890 --> 00:26:22,890
I don't know what your friend was like,
but I'm the one who's upset here!

411
00:26:22,890 --> 00:26:24,850
Maybe she's the copycat!

412
00:26:26,050 --> 00:26:28,340
Wh-What'd you say?!

413
00:26:28,340 --> 00:26:31,650
I see the exit! The harbor is right there!

414
00:26:36,860 --> 00:26:39,070
Hey, who is it now?

415
00:26:42,210 --> 00:26:43,310
You're finally here...

416
00:26:44,690 --> 00:26:46,580
Straw Hat Luffy.

417
00:27:00,930 --> 00:27:02,770
Inherited will...

418
00:27:02,770 --> 00:27:05,510
the tides of time,
and humanity's dreams...

419
00:27:05,510 --> 00:27:08,680
They cannot be stopped.

420
00:27:08,680 --> 00:27:11,730
As long as people seek freedom,

421
00:27:11,730 --> 00:27:14,480
these things will never cease to be.

422
00:27:15,530 --> 00:27:18,490
A pirate, huh? Fine by me.

423
00:27:25,910 --> 00:27:30,610
I'm Captain Smoker.
I run Loguetown for the Marines.

424
00:27:30,610 --> 00:27:32,500
You're under arrest.

425
00:27:32,500 --> 00:27:35,920
Huh? Arrest? Forget it!

426
00:27:35,920 --> 00:27:39,610
I'm on my way to the Grand Line
to become King of the Pirates!

427
00:27:39,610 --> 00:27:40,680
King of the Pirates?

428
00:27:41,050 --> 00:27:43,430
I refuse to get arrested
in a place like this!

429
00:27:43,820 --> 00:27:46,180
Then you'll have to beat me first.

430
00:27:46,590 --> 00:27:48,130
Hey, Luffy...

431
00:27:48,870 --> 00:27:52,020
Sanji, go on ahead. I'll be right there.

432
00:27:59,650 --> 00:28:00,790
Fire!

433
00:28:06,120 --> 00:28:07,990
Fire the cannons!

434
00:28:22,770 --> 00:28:26,470
If we stay here any longer,
the Going Merry will be sunk!

435
00:28:31,640 --> 00:28:35,100
Y-You're about to set sail?
Luffy and them aren't back yet!

436
00:28:35,550 --> 00:28:38,570
We're out of options!
It's better than getting sunk!

437
00:28:39,750 --> 00:28:41,730
Right rudder full!

438
00:28:44,860 --> 00:28:46,620
So what about Luffy's group?

439
00:28:46,620 --> 00:28:48,410
We'll pick them up later!

440
00:28:48,410 --> 00:28:50,790
Don't let them get away! Follow them!

441
00:28:50,790 --> 00:28:51,950
Nami!

442
00:28:52,640 --> 00:28:53,910
Sanji!

443
00:28:53,910 --> 00:28:54,800
Sanji!

444
00:28:54,800 --> 00:28:57,380
Nami, I'm back!

445
00:28:57,380 --> 00:28:59,250
Where're Luffy and Zoro?

446
00:28:59,760 --> 00:29:02,260
Can we even collect
those damn idiots?!

447
00:29:04,510 --> 00:29:05,450
Sanji!

448
00:29:05,450 --> 00:29:06,220
Behind you!

449
00:29:12,710 --> 00:29:14,640
Damn, there's no end to 'em!

450
00:29:14,640 --> 00:29:16,430
I'll cover him! Bring me closer!

451
00:29:16,430 --> 00:29:20,090
I can't! There's a strong current
keeping us from shore!

452
00:29:20,090 --> 00:29:21,690
Ah, screw it!

453
00:29:22,100 --> 00:29:22,940
Usopp!

454
00:29:22,940 --> 00:29:24,070
Bastards!

455
00:29:33,790 --> 00:29:35,790
Usopp! Sanji!

456
00:29:46,330 --> 00:29:47,970
What?! What?! What's going on?!

457
00:29:51,220 --> 00:29:56,490
I ate the Smoke-Smoke Fruit,
so my body become smoke at will!

458
00:30:14,590 --> 00:30:17,530
What's wrong? Had enough?

459
00:30:25,760 --> 00:30:29,220
Gum-Gum Gatling!

460
00:30:39,590 --> 00:30:42,930
What? Eww, that's gross!

461
00:30:47,010 --> 00:30:48,700
White Blow!

462
00:30:50,160 --> 00:30:51,940
You jerk!

463
00:30:51,940 --> 00:30:55,110
Gum-Gum Pistol!

464
00:30:56,150 --> 00:31:00,460
Get it now? You can't
enter the Grand Line.

465
00:31:01,250 --> 00:31:02,800
That's what I'm telling you!

466
00:31:08,170 --> 00:31:11,390
You're wanted for thirty million belly?

467
00:31:11,390 --> 00:31:14,150
Looks like you've run out
of your devil's luck.

468
00:31:16,690 --> 00:31:19,800
Don't be so sure.

469
00:31:19,800 --> 00:31:21,270
You're...

470
00:31:33,810 --> 00:31:36,250
Wh-What's happening? Who is it? Who's there?

471
00:31:37,290 --> 00:31:40,530
The government is after your head.

472
00:31:42,110 --> 00:31:45,960
The world is waiting for our answer.

473
00:32:20,590 --> 00:32:22,390
Th-This is...

474
00:32:24,890 --> 00:32:27,070
Wh-What just happened?

475
00:32:29,970 --> 00:32:32,050
Luffy!

476
00:32:32,310 --> 00:32:34,340
Luffy!

477
00:32:34,340 --> 00:32:35,830
Nami!

478
00:32:35,830 --> 00:32:38,430
We'd better hurry before
the ship is swept away!

479
00:32:38,430 --> 00:32:39,520
Alright!

480
00:32:40,850 --> 00:32:42,850
Gum-Gum...

481
00:32:45,730 --> 00:32:46,380
Wha...?!

482
00:32:46,380 --> 00:32:47,630
W-Wait!

483
00:32:47,630 --> 00:32:49,190
I have a bad feeling...

484
00:32:49,200 --> 00:32:52,530
Rocket!

485
00:32:51,120 --> 00:32:52,530
Ahhh, I knew it!

486
00:33:02,710 --> 00:33:03,790
Everyone...!

487
00:33:08,170 --> 00:33:12,000
Seriously, that flashy gust
was a lucky break.

488
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:15,380
This escape was possible because
I always keep my wits about me.

489
00:33:15,970 --> 00:33:17,500
Where to now?

490
00:33:17,500 --> 00:33:24,600
Let's head straight to
the Grand Line. How nostalgic!

491
00:33:35,150 --> 00:33:41,160
If that's your decision, then go!

492
00:33:41,490 --> 00:33:45,630
Why?! Why did you help that man...

493
00:33:45,630 --> 00:33:46,910
Dragon?!

494
00:33:50,430 --> 00:33:54,790
What reason would there be to
interfere with a man's departure?

495
00:34:05,370 --> 00:34:08,270
Set sail! We're going after Straw Hat!

496
00:34:08,270 --> 00:34:09,730
What?

497
00:34:10,370 --> 00:34:12,730
We're entering the Grand Line.

498
00:34:12,730 --> 00:34:16,370
B-But, Captain!
This island is your post.

499
00:34:16,370 --> 00:34:18,320
What would the higher-ups say?!

500
00:34:19,350 --> 00:34:22,530
Tell them I said,
"Don't order me around!"

501
00:34:23,350 --> 00:34:24,750
I'm coming with you!

502
00:34:24,750 --> 00:34:26,650
Sergeant Major Tashigi!

503
00:34:26,650 --> 00:34:29,540
I can't let Roronoa get away!

504
00:34:29,540 --> 00:34:32,540
I'll capture him without fail!

505
00:34:32,550 --> 00:34:35,550
Whoa! It feels like
the ship's gonna tip over!

506
00:34:39,330 --> 00:34:40,890
See that light?

507
00:34:40,890 --> 00:34:42,370
The island's lighthouse?

508
00:34:42,370 --> 00:34:43,810
It's a "guiding light."

509
00:34:43,810 --> 00:34:46,850
The entrance to the Grand Line
lies just beyond that light.

510
00:34:46,850 --> 00:34:49,590
The Grand Line is past that light...

511
00:34:49,590 --> 00:34:50,810
What do you wanna do?

512
00:34:50,810 --> 00:34:54,440
D-Do we have to enter
during a storm like this?

513
00:35:06,620 --> 00:35:11,010
Okay, then! Shall we hold a launch
ceremony for entering this great sea?

514
00:35:11,010 --> 00:35:11,960
Hey!

515
00:35:11,960 --> 00:35:12,860
Oh! Sounds good!

516
00:35:12,860 --> 00:35:14,630
Let's do it!

517
00:35:15,190 --> 00:35:18,340
To find the All Blue!

518
00:35:19,030 --> 00:35:21,510
To be King of the Pirates!

519
00:35:22,450 --> 00:35:24,850
To become the greatest swordsman!

520
00:35:25,990 --> 00:35:29,060
To draw a map of the world!

521
